info.author: Francesco Romani
classifiers: Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules
info.description:
A skip list is a data structure for storing a sorted list
        of items using a hierarchy of linked lists that connect increasingly
        sparse subsequences of the items. These auxiliary lists allow item
        lookup with efficiency comparable to balanced binary search trees (that
        is, with number of probes proportional to log n instead of n).
info.name: skiplist
info.summary: Skiplists are a simpler alternative to balanced binary trees
info.html_description:
A skip list is a data structure for storing a sorted list
of items using a hierarchy of linked lists that connect increasingly sparse subsequences of the items. These auxiliary lists allow item lookup with efficiency comparable to balanced binary search trees (that is, with number of probes proportional to log n instead of n).
